reviews.review: Yes its nostalgic... But for fans of over 40 years it hits every note, and it's fast paced action is enthralling.

I am no critic by any means, but I am a huge Star Wars fan and as one I can say with calm if my heart: Star Wars Episode IX I s the best one of the new trilogy also, of course  with no spoilers,  amazing conclusion of the Skywalker saga, action packed  full with story and amazing play, and oh DAMN THAT AMAZING FINAL!!!!!!

Go enjoy it, you won't regret  10/10!!!
Complete mess the JJ Abrams/ R Johnson mess continues with a cheesy script that's all Over the place and gives the impression it's been rushed together

They killed Star Wars with The Last Jedi & with The rise of Skywalker they desecrated the corpse in the worst way possible.
George Lucas deserve better then this!
A movie which struggles with the decisions of its predecessors. However, despite its complicated plot, I never found myself bored during the film

A pity that this film wants to please fans instead of offering something challenging. The previous episode left too many questions and the answers in this movie instead of being impressive, they end up being a glimpse into the past but with a lousy handling of the story being repetitive, just as The Force Awakens was. The development of the characters is poor since instead they exalt them for this closure, they end up being illogical and flat to have illogical motivations, meaningless situations or worse, some leave them without conclusion. This has been a disastrous trilogy where no chapter could be connected by the previous one and the mistake was to please an audience instead of bothering to tell a new and progressive story through its filmmakers.
All my questions were answered. Cant wait till 2022 for the next star wars film

Great movie, really fun and a solid wrap up to the sequels. 
Pacing is a bit intense at times but other than that feels a lot 
more like SW to me again.

Phenomenal. 

Did it cater to Star Wars fans? Yes. Of course it did. That's how movie franchises work. Every scene was magical. The effects were next level and the narrative offered a beautiful close in the story of Skywalker.

It was good but not great, although compared to The Last Jedi it was a masterpiece, still too many scenes and dialogue rebooted/stolen from the classic trilogy to be even considered great, Déjà Vu isn't something I look for in a movie. Jar Jar Abrams strikes again. If the next trilogy doesent offer us something totally new and unseen before then the whole franchise will slowly die a painful death, people dont want to keep buying the same regurgitated material over and over again.
